args: Ah, perfect! If I may, let me\nbend your ears for a minute.
I have someone for you to meet...
Ah, the dragon from another world, yes?
To be more accurate, she's a manakete.\nBut yes, essentially.
She's a cute little thing, isn't she?\nWell, it must have been quite the trial\nto come to a different world like this.
Yes, but I'll be fine so long as\nmy big sis Mym is here!
In a manner of speaking, yes.\nThat's why I'm making introductions—\nit seemed the sisterly thing to do.
Stow it, buddy! I don't have time for\nyour skepticism! ...Ahem! Right then.\nTime for some proper introductions.
Tiki, the cheeky one there is Jupiter,\nand the nice one is Mercury.
And who might you be, little one?
The one from another world? Well,\nyou certainly have lots of vim and vigor.
That's because I'm having a great time\nwith all the dragons in this world!
I told my big sis Mym I wanted to make\nlots of friends, so she's helping me do it!
Ugh. Please not this again.\nJust introduce yourself already.
I am called Zodiark the Shadowwyrm.\nI am he who waltzes in the black!\nI am darkness incarnate!
That's the same tired line you used\nwhen you forged your pact.
Try it again, maybe—and be friendlier!\nYou're scaring poor Tiki half to death.
Zodiark is just like my Ban-Ban! Hee hee!\nCan I call you Grandpa Zod-Zod?
Aaaah ha ha ha! I LOVE IT!\nOl' Grandpa Zod-Zod!
What is behind your desire to\ngive me such a name, child?
Well, you're kind of like Bantu,\nand I call him Ban-Ban!
And is this Bantu your grandfather?
Yeah! Well, but he's a fire dragon,\nso he's a little different from me.
Her only family in her home world\nwas a manakete named Bantu.
I see. In that case, I suppose you\nmay call me whatever you see fit.
Yes? You seem a little shocked there.
Nothing like that, I assure you.
Now I have more friends AND\na bigger family! It's great!
Do none of you have family?
I've never really thought about it.\nI've always lived carefree on my own.
I've been much the same—though ever\nsince I met my darling, my family plans\nfor the future have been growing.
As for me, the people of Saint Lotier\nare all my children.
But in terms of a ＂dragon family,＂\nI can't really picture one.
There are all manner of dragons as well.

Though there may be those like Simurgh
who praise the bonds between a parent
and a child, there are others who want
nothing to do with such things.
Do YOU have any family,\nGrandpa Zod-Zod?
I know not if it would be suitable to call\nthem family, but I do have some who\nare quite dear to me.
Yeah! Being alone is so lonely.\nTrust me—I know all about it.
I can't say I really understand what all\nof this ＂family＂ stuff is about...
Which is why I'll join yours so I can\nfinally understand what's going on!
Would it be all right if I\njoined in as well, Tiki?
Of course! I want the huuugest family\nthat I can possibly get!
Well, you've got a big sister in Brunhilda\nand a feeble old grandpa in Zod-Zod.\nIn that case, I will beeee..
Then I suppose the title\nof ＂mother＂ falls to me.
Well, this is all just fantastic!\n...Oh, and before I forget,\nTiki is older than all of us.
Yep! She's super ancient—although now\nthat I think on it, Zodiark miiight be older\nthan she is, maybe?
Geez! Looks like you're MY big sister,\nTiki! Sorry about that.
Oh, and your adorable little brother would\nlike you to get some dragon fruits from\nCleo, please. 'K thaaaanks!
Jupiter, you must not speak to someone\nabove your station in such a disrespectful\ntone. It simply will not do.
Are you kidding me? She's THRILLED to\ndote on her cute little brother! Riiiight?
Don't worry about that troublesome one,\nBig Sister. Here, let me give you a wing\nmassage.
